### Class Diagram Notation

```
A <|-- B     : A inherits from B
A *-- B      : A contains B (composition)
A o-- B      : A has B (aggregation)
A --> B      : A uses B (dependency)
A -- B       : A relates to B (association)
```

### Module Diagram Notation

In module diagrams, arrows indicate dependencies between modules:

```
A --> B      : Module A depends on Module B
```
